INSERT INTO `content_props` VALUES ('85', '<div class=\"WordSection1\">\r\n<h1 class=\"heading\">Booking Conditions</h1>\r\n<p><strong>The contract:</strong> Please read these booking conditions carefully and make sure you have understood them as well as the itinerary and style of the trip you are booking. In completing and submitting the booking form, you agree to these conditions, which constitute the agreement between Spirit Asia Travel (SAT) and the client. No person other than a director of SAT has the authority to modify these booking conditions.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Booking:</strong> Booking is in effect when SAT accepts your completed booking form and payment of the non-refundable deposit or full-payment. Acceptance of your booking will be confirmed in writing to you or your travel agent. A contract will exist between us from the date we issue the confirmation invoice. Please refer to your booking confirmation invoice for details regarding final payments. Payment of the balance of the trip price is due 42 days before the departure date. If this balance is not paid on or before the due date we reserve the right to treat your booking as cancelled.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Payment:</strong> Bookings made less than 42 days prior to departure must be paid for in full at the time of booking. A 3% surcharge will be levied if the final balance / full payment is made by credit card. However, if you are booking more than 42 days prior to the scheduled date of departure you will need to send 20% of the total cost of the trip as deposit, If the full tour price is not paid 42 days before departure, your booking may be cancelled without notice and the cancellation charges set out in conditions of cancellation will be applicable.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Prices and Validity:</strong> Prices advertised in the website are subject to change. Package prices are based on ground costs, exchange rates and assumptions made at the time of publication. SAT tries its utmost not to increase tour prices, however sometimes increases are outside our control, therefore, we reserve the right to modify tour prices at any time before and including the departure date for reasons such as fluctuations in exchange rates, increases in airfares or other transportation costs, taxes, fuel costs or increases in ground operator service fees or if government action should require us to do so. Any increase in tour prices must be paid prior to the departure date.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cancellations:</strong> If you wish to cancel your booking, notification of cancellation must be made to SAT in writing. The date of the cancellation is the date on which SAT receives written notification. It is your responsibility to ensure that notification is received by us. You will be liable to pay cancellation charges - based on hotel and transportation contract policies, administration fees and tour guide booking – These fees apply as follows, per person:</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<table class=\"table\" style=\"margin-top: 13px;\" width=\"100%\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr class=\"white\"><th>Number of days before departure when we receive your cancellation</th><th>Charge as percentage of your booking tour price or deposit, whichever is greater</th></tr>\r\n<tr class=\"grey\">\r\n<td>42 days or more</td>\r\n<td>loss of deposit</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr class=\"white\">\r\n<td>41 - 35 days    </td>\r\n<td>25 %</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr class=\"grey\">\r\n<td>34 - 28 days   </td>\r\n<td>50 %</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr class=\"white\">\r\n<td>27 - 15 days  </td>\r\n<td>75 %</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr class=\"grey\">\r\n<td style=\"padding: 10px 0 10px 13px;\">14 days or less  </td>\r\n<td style=\"padding: 10px 0 10px 13px;\">100 %</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>Cancellation by SAT:</strong> We will not cancel your trip unless we are forced to do so by circumstances beyond our control ‘’force majeure’’ - such as (but not limited to) war, threat of war, riot, civil strife, industrial dispute, unavoidable technical problems with transport, terrorist activity, natural or nuclear disaster, fire, adverse weather conditions, sickness, quarantine – or because the minimum number of bookings needed to operate the tour have not been reached. With any form of cancellation, SAT will offer you alternative arrangements, and if the price of your alternative booking is of lower value than the original booking we will refund you the difference. If the alternative tour chosen is of a higher value then you will pay the difference in price. If due to ‘’force majeure’’ or governmental travel warning or advice, SAT reserves the right to cancel a departure at any time and conditions of refund applies as mentioned in the conditions of cancellation, your travel insurance may compensate you depending on the circumstances. If due to insufficient numbers of participants SAT will not cancel your trip less than 14 days prior the date of departure and if you do not accept alternative arrangements we will refund all payments you have made to SAT except any unrecoverable costs such as (but not limited to) bank transfer. SAT is not liable for any incidental expenses that you may have incurred as a result of your booking such as visas, vaccinations, flights etc…</p>\r\n<p><strong>Change to your trip:</strong> You acknowledge that travelling with SAT requires a degree of flexibility, an open mind, and an understanding that the itinerary, accommodation and modes of transport are subject to change without prior notice, even after a tour’s commencement, due to local circumstances. Changes in itinerary may be caused by ‘’force majeure’’, poor road conditions, weather, availability of tickets, vehicle breakdowns, changes in transport schedules, or other circumstances beyond SAT’s control or which simply cannot be foreseen. If any such change necessitates additional costs (including accommodation or ground transportation, flights in extreme case) to be charged, you agree that you will pay these additional costs as required by SAT. SAT does not accept any responsibility for delays or compensation resulting from circumstances beyond its control. You are aware that information about trips given in our website and the trip notes are also subject to change.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Authority of the leader:</strong> While travelling with SAT, you agree to accept the authority of the leader, who represents SAT, and local operator at all times. You are aware that travel within a group may involve compromise to accommodate the diverse needs/desires and physical abilities of other group members. Be aware that illegal use of drugs, use of prostitutes and racist behaviour toward people in the group or local people is not tolerated. If you commit any illegal act when on tour or if in the opinion of the leader your behaviour is causing or likely to cause danger, distress or annoyance to others, the leader reserves the right to terminate your travel arrangements and order you to leave the tour immediately with no right of refund and without any liability on our part.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Insurance:</strong> Travel Insurance is compulsory. You have to be covered, at least, for accidents, injury, illness and fatality medical expenses, including any related to pre-existing medical conditions, emergency repatriation (including helicopter rescue and air ambulance where applicable) and personal liability. Your travel insurance must be valid for the entire duration of the tour. Please bring a copy of your travel insurance policy as well as the insurance company’s 24hours emergency contact number to give to your tour leader in case of illness. If you join the holiday without adequate insurance, you may not be allowed to continue on the holiday, with no right of refund.  Please, be sure to be able to present the appropriate documents during the group meeting on the first day of your trip. Note that The Spirit of Asia Travel is unable to accept insurance provided by a credit card issuer. You are also strongly advised to be covered for cancellation, curtailment and loss of luggage and personal effects, as Spirit Asia Travel shall not be held liable.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Travel documents: </strong>Any information or advice provided by SAT on matters such as permits, visas, vaccination, climate, clothing, baggage, special equipment, etc… is given in good faith but without liability on our part. It is entirely your responsibility to obtain the relevant medical advice and vaccinations and to ensure you have all the necessary travel documentation required for the holiday.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><strong>Passport and visas: </strong>You must carry a valid passport and have obtained all of the appropriate visas, permits and certificates for the countries in which you will visit during your trip. Your passport must be valid for six months beyond the duration of the trip. It is your responsibility to ensure that you are in possession of the correct visas, permits and certificates for your trip; please refer to the Travel Tips for details. We are not responsible if you are refused entry to a country because you lack the correct passport, visa or other travel documentation. INSERT INTO `content_props` VALUES ('85', '1', null);
