INSERT INTO `content_props` VALUES ('137', '<p><strong>Day 1: Siem Reap</strong></p>\r\n<p>There are many direct flies to Siem Reap, Cambodia via Bangkok, Singapore, Malaysia and other destinations. Today followed by visit the complex of Angkor Wat, the largest and most impressive of all the temples by tuk tuk. We will ride elephants to the hilltop temple ofPhnom Bakheng, climb the imposing remains and enjoy a truly memorable sunset. Meals: Welcome dinner</p>\r\n<p><strong>Day 2: Angkor ~ 30 km cycling (Need to check again for Km)</strong></p>\r\n<p>Today we will ride our bicycles to the temples complex, first the jungle temple of <strong>Ta Prohm, </strong>Victory gate and <strong>Angkor Thom</strong><strong>.</strong> Beginning with the Elephant Terrace and the Terrace of Leper King and <strong>Bayon,</strong> a pyramid temple decorated by about 200 gigantic carved heads, we move on to the “grand circuit” to see more temples of the Angkor Era, such as <strong>Preah Khan</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>Neak Pean, Ta Som</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>East Mebon, Pre Rup</strong> and <strong>Banteay Kdei</strong>. Meals: B, L, D (Picnic lunch will arrange around Angkor Area)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Day 3: Banteay Srey ~ 75 km cycling (Need to check again) </strong></p>\r\n<p>This morning we will cycle through the countryside, to the magnificent <strong>Banteay Srei</strong> temple – the Citadel of women, decorated with superbly intricate reliefs of male and female divinities. We will stop at the <strong>Cambodian Landmine museum and Rehabilitation Centre</strong> before return back to our hotel. Meals: B, L, D (Picnic lunch will arrange around Angkor Area)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Day 4: Countryside ~ 40 km cycling (Need to check)</strong></p>\r\n<p>We will cycle through the bucolic countryside of Siem Reap and cross villages before we reach the Me Chrey floating village. We will enjoy a boat ride around the floating community. On the way back we will stop at <strong>Sangkheum Center for Children</strong>and<strong>Western Baray</strong>, an ancient reservoir. Meals: B, L, D with traditional show</p>\r\n<p><strong>Day 5: End of tour</strong></p>\r\n<p>The tour end after breakfast, you will have free time to explore central town or relax at the hotel before flight out. There are international flights to Bangkok or Vietnam and many other Asian destinations. Meals: B</p>\r\n<p><strong>Service included:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Accommodation twin share basis with daily breakfast and all kind of tax</p>\r\n<p>An experienced English-speaking local guide</p>\r\n<p>All ground transportation as mention on the itinerary (Tuk Tuk and private Air-con Vehicles)</p>\r\n<p>Sightseeing fee during guiding</p>\r\n<p>Meals as stated on the itinerary (B: Breakfast, L: Lunch, D: Dinner)</p>\r\n<p>Water during the tours</p>\r\n<p>Boat trip onto Tonle Sap Lake</p>\r\n<p>Shadow puppets show &amp; Traditional dancing show</p>\r\n<p>Use of mountain bikes for cycle</p>\r\n<p>Support vehicle for long trips</p>\r\n<p>Arrival &amp; Departure transfer</p>\r\n<p><strong>Service excluded:</strong></p>\r\n<p>All airfare, airport taxes and excess baggage charges</p>\r\n<p>All kind of own expenses</p>\r\n<p>Visa, Visa fee and vaccination charges</p>\r\n<p>Departure tax (25$)</p>\r\n<p>Personal travel insurance (compulsory)</p>\r\n<p>Helmet for cycling (recommended)</p>\r\n<p>All optional tours &amp; activities during free time</p>\r\n<p>All beverages during the included meals</p>\r\n<p>Expenditure of a personal nature, such as souvenir, laundry, postage, phone calls</p>\r\n<p>Tips</p>\r\n<p> </p>', null);
